---
/**
 * Privacy Policy Page
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="DigiHoof privacy policy. Learn how we handle user data and imaging information on our hoof radiograph reporting platform."
>

<section class="split-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p class="operator-notice">Effective date: June 15, 2026. DigiHoof is operated by DigiScan LLC.</p>

    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof is a hoof radiograph reporting platform operated by DigiScan LLC. This Privacy
      Policy explains how we collect, use, protect, and disclose information when clinics,
      veterinarians, farriers, staff members, and invited collaborators use DigiHoof. We designed
      this policy to be clear about a central point: your uploaded studies and reports are not
      sold, published, or distributed as third-party content. We use data to operate, support,
      secure, troubleshoot, evaluate, and improve DigiHoof.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      We may collect account and clinic information such as names, email addresses, clinic names,
      roles, authentication details, subscription status, billing status, and support requests.
      We may collect uploaded and generated clinical workflow data such as radiographs, DICOM
      files, photographs, image metadata, horse names, owner names, study dates, annotations,
      landmarks, measurements, labels, reports, notes, share links, and related workflow history.
      We also collect technical data such as device and browser information, IP addresses, log
      data, security events, usage events, performance data, cookies, and similar information
      needed to operate and protect the platform.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Use of Data</h2>
    <p>
      We use information to provide DigiHoof, process uploads, generate and store reports,
      authenticate users, manage subscriptions, provide support, troubleshoot problems, detect
      abuse, protect security, maintain audit logs, communicate with users, comply with legal
      obligations, and improve the platform. We may also use uploaded images, metadata,
      annotations, reports, support interactions, and workflow events for internal quality
      assurance, internal research, product development, measurement validation, model
      evaluation, model improvement, workflow analysis, and solving problems related to clinic
      interactions.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Clinic Ownership and Our Limited Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Clinics and authorized users retain ownership of uploaded imaging data and generated
      reports. DigiHoof does not claim ownership of clinical imaging content or reports. By using
      DigiHoof, you authorize DigiScan LLC to host, store, copy, process, display, transform,
      analyze, transmit, and otherwise use your data only as reasonably needed to provide,
      maintain, secure, support, troubleshoot, improve, and develop DigiHoof and related
      services, and as described in this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Service.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Internal Research and Product Improvement</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof may evaluate studies and related workflow data internally to improve image
      handling, measurement tools, model performance, error detection, user experience, support
      workflows, and report quality. This includes using data to understand why an upload failed,
      why an image was misclassified, whether landmarks or measurements need improvement, and how
      clinics interact with the platform. Where reasonably practical, we use de-identified,
      pseudonymized, aggregated, or minimized data for internal research and improvement. Internal
      review may still require limited access to identifiable studies when necessary for support,
      troubleshooting, quality assurance, security, or resolving a clinic-specific issue.
    </p>

    <h2>6. No Sale or Public Distribution of Studies</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell Clinic Data. We do not rent Clinic Data. We do not publish or distribute
      identifiable radiographs, DICOM studies, photographs, reports, horse information, owner
      information, or clinic case materials to the public, other clinics, marketing audiences, or
      unrelated third parties without permission. We may disclose information only as described in
      this policy, including to operate the service, use trusted service providers, comply with
      law, protect rights and safety, investigate abuse, complete business transactions, or act
      with your direction or consent.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Service Providers and Subprocessors</h2>
    <p>
      We may use trusted service providers for cloud hosting, data storage, image processing,
      inference, email, payments, analytics, monitoring, error logging, customer support,
      security, and related operations. These providers may process information only as needed to
      provide services to DigiHoof and are expected to handle information under appropriate
      confidentiality, security, or data-protection obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Sharing Directed by Users</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof may let users share reports, images, or links with clients, farriers, clinic team
      members, and other collaborators. When you choose to share information, the recipients you
      select may be able to view, download, print, screenshot, forward, or otherwise use that
      information. You are responsible for deciding whether a recipient is authorized to receive
      shared materials.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Security Measures</h2>
    <p>
      We use safeguards designed to protect information from unauthorized access, alteration,
      disclosure, or destruction, including access controls, authentication, encryption in
      transit, logging, infrastructure security, and operational controls. No internet-connected
      service can guarantee absolute security, and users are responsible for maintaining account
      security, strong passwords, and appropriate access controls within their clinic.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      We retain information for as long as needed to provide DigiHoof, maintain records, comply
      with legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, support clinics, preserve
      audit history, and protect the service. Clinics may request deletion of account or study
      data, subject to legal, contractual, backup, security, audit, billing, and legitimate
      operational retention needs. Deleted data may persist for a limited time in backups or logs
      before it is overwritten or removed according to normal retention cycles.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Veterinary Records and Client Information</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof is intended for veterinary and hoof-care workflow use. Users are responsible for
      complying with professional obligations, client confidentiality duties, record-retention
      laws, and veterinary medical record rules that apply in their jurisdiction. Do not upload
      human medical images or human protected health information to DigiHoof.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Cookies and Technical Tracking</h2>
    <p>
      We may use cookies, local storage, session tokens, analytics events, and similar
      technologies to keep users signed in, secure accounts, remember preferences, measure
      performance, understand feature usage, and operate the platform. Browser controls may allow
      you to limit some cookies, but certain features may not work without them.
    </p>

    <h2>13. International Data Processing</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof is operated from the United States and may use cloud infrastructure or service
      providers in the United States or other jurisdictions. By using DigiHoof, you understand
      that information may be processed and stored outside your state, province, or country,
      where privacy laws may differ.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may have rights to request access, correction, deletion,
      portability, restriction, objection, or information about certain processing activities.
      We will respond to applicable privacy requests as required by law. We may need to verify
      your identity and authority before fulfilling a request, especially when the request
      involves clinic records or another user's account.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Legal Disclosures</h2>
    <p>
      We may disclose information if we believe in good faith that disclosure is required by law,
      subpoena, court order, legal process, regulatory request, professional obligation, or to
      protect the rights, property, safety, security, or integrity of DigiScan LLC, DigiHoof,
      users, patients, clients, or others.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Business Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      If DigiScan LLC or DigiHoof is involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, restructuring,
      sale of assets, bankruptcy, or similar transaction, information may be transferred or
      disclosed as part of that transaction, subject to appropriate confidentiality or privacy
      protections where reasonably available.
    </p>

    <h2>17. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updated policies will be posted on
      this page. Continued use of DigiHoof after an update means the updated policy applies to
      future use of the platform.
    </p>

    <h2>18. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy inquiries, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:digihoof@digiscan.vet">digihoof@digiscan.vet</a>
      or visit our <a href="/support">support page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
